DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       This  function will set the maximum transfer unit of the transport that
       DTLS packets are sent over. Note that this should exclude  the  IP  (or
       IPv6)  and UDP headers. So for DTLS over IPv6 on an Ethenet device with
       MTU 1500, the DTLS MTU set with this function would be 1500 - 40  (IPV6
       header) - 8 (UDP header) = 1452.

